==English==

===Etymology===
From French [[automatique]], from {{Gr.}} '''[[αυτοματικός]]''' {{italbrac|automatikos}}, from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[αυτόματον]]''' {{italbrac|automaton}}, neutral of '''[[αυτόματος]]''' {{italbrac|automatos}} “selfmoving, moving of oneself, self-acting, spontaneous”, from '''[[αυτός]]''' {{italbrac|autos}} “self, myself” + '''[[μέμαα]]''' {{italbrac|memaa}} “to wish eagerly, strive, yearn, desire”.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˌɔːtəˈmætɪk/}}, {{SAMPA|/%O:t@"m{tIk/}}
*{{audio|en-us-automatic.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ætɪk|-ætɪk]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Capable of operating without external control or intervention.
#: ''The automatic clothes washer was a great labor-saving device''
# Acting out of habit; without conscious thought.
#: ''My reaction of fear was automatic.''
# Describes a firearm which fires continuously as long as the trigger is pressed and [[ammunition]] is not exhausted. Used regarding [[machine pistol]]s, [[submachine gun]]s, or [[machine gun]]s.

